member.name: M:Aspose.Diagram.License.SetLicense(System.String)
member.summary: Licenses the component.

remarks.p: Tries to find the license in the following locations:

ms.p: 2. The folder of the component assembly.
3. The folder of the client's calling assembly.
4. The folder of the entry assembly.
5. An embedded resource in the client's calling assembly.
Note:On the .NET Compact Framework, tries to find the license only in these locations:
2. An embedded resource in the client's calling assembly.

java.p: 2. The folder of the component jar file.

member.example:
In this example, an attempt will be made to find a license file named MyLicense.lic in the folder that contains
the component, in the folder that contains the calling assembly, in the folder of the entry assembly and then in the embedded resources of the calling assembly.
[C#]
License license = new License(); license.SetLicense("MyLicense.lic");
[Visual Basic]
Dim license As License = New License license.SetLicense("MyLicense.lic")
the component jar file:
License license = new License(); license.setLicense("MyLicense.lic"); Can be a full or short file name or name of an embedded resource. Use an empty string to switch to evaluation mode.

member.summary: Allows assembling the document: inserting, rotating, or deleting pages and creating navigation elements such as bookmarks or thumbnail images. When using RC4 40-bit encryption, this option is ignored and document assembly is allowed when ModifyContents is set.

member.name: F:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.PdfPermissions.HighResolutionPrinting

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.CoordinateCollection.ArcToCol
member.summary: Contains the x- and y-coordinates and bow of a circular arc represented respectively by the X, Y, and A elements.

member.summary: Contains elements specifying the x- and y-coordinates of two points on an infinite line. The X and Y elements specify the x- and y-coordinates of the first point, and the A and B elements specify the x- and y-coordinates of the second point.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.CoordinateCollection.EllipseCol
member.summary: Contains elements specifying the x- and y-coordinates of the ellipse's center point and two points on the ellipse.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.CoordinateCollection.EllipticalArcToCol
member.summary: Contains elements that specify information about an elliptical arc.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.CoordinateCollection.SplineStartCol
member.summary: Contains x- and y-coordinates for a spline's second control point, its second knot, its first knot, the last knot, and the degree of the spline. This information is contained in the X, Y, A, B, C, and D elements, respectively.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.CoordinateCollection.SplineKnotCol
member.summary: Contains x- and y-coordinates for a spline's control point and a spline's knot, represented by the X, Y, and A elements, respectively.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.CoordinateCollection.PolylineToCol
member.summary: Contains x- and y-coordinates of the last point of a polyline and a polyline formula. The coordinates are specified in the X and Y elements, and the formula is specified in the A element.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.CoordinateCollection.NURBSToCol
member.summary: Contains the x- and y-coordinates, position of the second to last knot, position of the last weight, position of the first knot, position of the first weight, and the formula for a nonuniform rational B-spline (NURBS). This information is specified in the X, Y, A, B, C, D, and E elements, respectively.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.CoordinateCollection.RelMoveToCol
member.summary: Contains the x- and y-coordinates of the first vertex of a shape, or contains the x- and y-coordinates of the first vertex after a break in a path.Coordinates are specified as relative coordinates.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.CoordinateCollection.RelLineToCol
member.summary: Contains x- and y-coordinates of the ending vertex of a straight line segment. These coordinates are contained in the X and Y elements, respectively.Coordinates are specified as relative coordinates.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.ImageBrightness
member.summary: Gets or sets the brightness for the the generated images.
member.remarks:
This property has effect only when saving to raster image formats.
The default value is 0.5. The value must be in the range between 0 and 1.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.ImageColorMode
member.summary: Gets or sets the color mode for the generated images.
member.remarks:
This property has effect only when saving to raster image formats.
The default value is None.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.ImageContrast
member.summary: Gets or sets the contrast for the generated images.
member.remarks:
This property has effect only when saving to raster image formats.
The default value is 0.5. The value must be in the range between 0 and 1.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.JpegQuality
member.summary: Gets or sets a value determining the quality of the generated JPEG images.
member.remarks:
Has effect only when saving to JPEG.
Use this property to get or set the quality of generated images when saving in JPEG format. The value may vary from 0 to 100 where 0 means worst quality but maximum compression and 100 means best quality but minimum compression.
The default value is 95.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.PageCount
member.summary: Gets or sets the number of pages to render when saving to a multipage TIFF file. Default is MaxValue which means all pages of the diagram will be rendered.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.PageIndex
member.summary: Gets or sets the 0-based index of the first page to render. Default is 0.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.ExportHiddenPage
member.summary: Defines whether need exporting the hidden page or not.
member.remarks: Default value is true.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.Resolution
member.summary: Gets or sets the resolution for the generated images, in dots per inch.
member.remarks:
This property has effect only when saving to raster image formats.
The default value is 96.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.SaveFormat
member.summary: Specifies the format in which the rendered diagram pages will be saved if this save options object is used. Can be Tiff, Png, Bmp, Emf or Jpeg.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.Scale
member.summary: Gets or sets the zoom factor for the generated images.
member.remarks: The default value is 1.0. The value must be greater than 0.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.ContentZoom
member.summary: This parameter is similar with scale, but not effect the generated image size.
member.remarks: The default value is 1.0. The value must be greater than 0.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.TiffCompression
member.summary: Gets or sets the type of compression to apply when saving generated images to the TIFF format.
member.remarks:
Has effect only when saving to TIFF.
The default value is Lzw.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.SaveForegroundPagesOnly
member.summary: Specifies whether all pages will be saved in image or only foreground.
member.remarks: If true - rendered only foreground pages(with background if present). If false - rendered foreground pages(with background if present) after that empty background pages. Can return true only when PageCount > 1. The default value is false.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.SameAsPdfConversionArea
member.summary: Specifies whether saving area same as pdf .
member.remarks: If true - rendered area same as pdf. If false - rendered area default. The default value is false.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.PixelOffsetMode
member.summary: Gets or set a value specifying how pixels are offset during rendering.
member.remarks:
This property has effect only when saving to raster image formats.
The default value is Default.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.SmoothingMode
member.summary: Specifies whether smoothing (antialiasing) is applied to lines and curves and the edges of filled areas.
member.remarks:
This property has effect only when saving to raster image formats.
The default value is Default.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.CompositingQuality
member.summary: Specifies the quality level to use during compositing.
member.remarks:
This property has effect only when saving to raster image formats.
The default value is Default.

member.name: P:Aspose.Diagram.Saving.ImageSaveOptions.InterpolationMode
member.summary: Specifies the algorithm that is used when images are scaled or rotated.
member.remarks:
This property has effect only when saving to raster image formats.
